<% content_for :title, "Terms & Privacy" %>

<header class="mb-6">
  <h1 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Terms &amp; Privacy</h1>
  <p class="mt-0.5 text-sm text-ink-muted">How Switchboard works, what it holds, and what you are responsible for.</p>
</header>

<div class="max-w-3xl">
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-copper-dim/40 bg-copper/5 px-4 py-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    <span class="font-medium text-ink">The short version.</span>
    Switchboard is a non-custodial marketplace built on Nostr and Cashu: we never hold your keys or your funds,
    and every order is escrowed. Your activity on Nostr is public, and escrowed sats are held by a mint you
    choose. It is early, independent software we are actively hardening, and your
    <a href="<%= donate_path %>" class="font-medium text-copper hover:text-copper-bright">donations</a>
    help us make it more robust and reliable.
  </div>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">What Switchboard is</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    Switchboard is software for discovering services and open requests published on the Nostr network and for
    coordinating escrowed payments in Cashu ecash over Lightning. It is a tool, not a party to your transactions.
    Buyers and sellers deal directly with each other.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Your keys and your funds (non-custodial)</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    Your Nostr private key, your Cashu tokens, escrow preimages, and unlock material stay in your browser and
    never reach our servers. We cannot move, freeze, refund, or recover your funds, and we cannot reset or
    recover your key. You are solely responsible for safeguarding your key and for backing up the escrow unlock
    material an order gives you. Lose it and the funds for that order may be unrecoverable.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Escrow and the Cashu mint</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    While an order is funded, the backing sats are held as ecash by a third-party Cashu mint that you select
    from the allowlist. That mint is a custodian of those sats: it could go offline, fail, be seized, change its
    terms, or refuse to redeem. Switchboard does not operate the mint, does not control it, and is not liable for
    its conduct or solvency. Choose a mint you trust, and prefer small amounts.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Nostr is public</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    Listings, requests, profile details, and other events you publish are signed with your key and broadcast to
    independent relays you do not control. They are public, may be copied and re-published by anyone, and cannot
    be guaranteed to be deleted once sent. Do not publish anything you are not comfortable making permanent and
    public.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">What we store, and what we do not</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    To run the order ledger we store observable, non-secret data: order amounts, escrow lock terms, the public
    keys of the parties, and timestamps, plus a session record when you sign in. We never store private keys,
    escrow preimages, spendable proofs, or the plaintext of your encrypted messages. Private messages are
    end-to-end encrypted between you and the other party.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Disputes and mediation</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    Some orders use a mediated (2-of-3) escrow in which a platform arbiter can co-sign to resolve a dispute.
    Mediation is a best effort to reach a fair outcome and is not a guarantee. In every case the buyer keeps a
    refund path that opens after the escrow locktime passes.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Our commitment, and its limits</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    We build the money path carefully and review it adversarially. Still, no software is perfect and operations
    on Bitcoin and Cashu are irreversible, so we offer Switchboard as independent, early software without a
    guarantee and cannot accept liability for a counterparty's conduct or for a mint or relay failing.
    <a href="<%= donate_path %>" class="font-medium text-copper hover:text-copper-bright">Supporting the project</a>
    directly funds the testing, audits, and infrastructure that make it more dependable over time.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Acceptable use</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    Do not use Switchboard for anything illegal where you are, for fraud, or to harm others. You are responsible
    for complying with the laws and taxes that apply to you.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-8 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Changes and contact</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
    These terms may change as the software evolves; continued use means you accept the current version. Questions
    or concerns: reach us on Nostr at
    <a href="https://njump.me/npub18rl8k26jzhjq572k3ys93z6csmtzz7jr2uxz3s9r9cmtzg3wjq0q4z92mq"
       target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
       class="font-medium text-copper hover:text-copper-bright">our profile</a>.
  </p>
</div>
